"Information security is now such a critical part of an organisation's ability to manage risk that it pays to have skilled and knowledgeable people on hand to guide, advise and deal with issues. But as everyone knows, cyber security skills are in short supply and firms have trouble hanging on to the experienced security experts they have. So what do they do about this? In this interview, Matt Lorentzen, principal security consultant at Trustwave SpiderLabs, outlines the current state of in-house security skills within organisations, where they're falling short and what can be done about it, particularly in terms of upskilling existing staff."
